                                                   Gala closing on the cards
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The second edition of the Indian Premier League (IPL) will witness a star-studded closing ceremony after the final match on Sunday at the Wanderers.         
	In what promises to be a fitting finale to the cash-awash event, stars from Bollywood will join hands with American R amp;B singing sensation Akon and Carribean music legend Eddy Grant to enthral the crowds.         
	Bollywood superstars Shilpa Shetty and Katrina Kaif are part of a star studded line-up which will perform at the end of the IPL final. Grant will be rendering some of his all-time hits, while Akon will perform a selection from his albums. Other notable performers of the night include renowned percussionist Shivamani and a group of Indian and South African drummers.                                                                                                                       
